# File: stylesheets/screen.css.ab
# Purpose: Compiled mobile/responsive application stylesheet in the default Compass output directory (stylesheets/)
# Dependencies: []

## Overview
A compiled CSS stylesheet for mobile/responsive views located in the default Compass `stylesheets/` output directory at the project root. Compiled using Ruby 2.3.0 with RVM (`~/.rvm/gems/ruby-2.3.0/gems/compass-core-1.0.3`). Begins with the full Compass CSS reset followed by ProximaNova font declarations and application component styles (navbar, cards, buttons, etc.).

This file appears to be an earlier Compass compilation output from the project root's `config.rb`, before the project standardized on `app/assets/css/` as the stylesheet output directory.

## Interface
No exports. Stylesheet file — not actively loaded by the running application (the `app/assets/css/screen.css` version is canonical).

## Dependencies
No project-level `.ab` dependencies. Requires ProximaNova font files at `../fonts/proximanova-*.ttf` (resolved relative to `stylesheets/`).

## Implementation Notes
- Compiled with Compass using RVM Ruby 2.3.0 on macOS/Linux
- Compass source comment path: `../../../../../../.rvm/gems/ruby-2.3.0/gems/compass-core-1.0.3/`
- Contains Compass CSS reset + ProximaNova fonts + application styles
- Default Compass output directory — generated when `compass compile` is run from the project root with the default `config.rb`
- The `app/assets/css/screen.css` is the current active version
